                <h1>Understanding Theoretical Background in Research</h1>
                <p>Theoretical background refers to the foundational principles and frameworks that support a specific field of study or research. It encompasses key theories, models, and relevant literature that help explain phenomena and guide investigations. Understanding this background is essential for contextualizing new findings and building upon established knowledge.</p>
